<br>
I had thought closing the Council of Arcana would have been the correct thing to do. Yet I have found in my heart that I am unable to do such. I had thought to offer an opportunity for those, whom I am dearly blessed by their loyalty, to move on had they wished, yet none did. After speaking with the members and thanks to the heartfelt expressions of support from all of thee, I find I am unable to close my Family. I apologize for my folly and for littering thy webpage with my initial announcement. I crave thy pardon all <br>
<br>
It is with an open and cheerful heart that I formally announce the Council of Arcana will remain on Quellious for a long time to come.<br>
<br>
The Council hast never been a guild to recruit, yet I would offer that if thou art interested in joining a guild committed to helping others without compensation, we art the Family for thee. I would also offer if thou art interested in seeking to give back to others that have aided thee and to help make Quellious a better playing environment for all, to consider the Council of Arcana.<br>
<br>
We all remember the joy of a volunteer willing to resurrect us, or a simple SOW, or a drive-by buff that, although a small act for the caster, made a real difference in that playing day for the recipient. <br>
<br>
That is the calling of the Council. <br>
<br>
If thou dost have a lower character that thou wouldst wish to spend some time once a week or so as either a rescue player, or a healing-resurrecting-buffing player for those in need, pray consider the Council of Arcana.<br>
<br>
If thou dost feel the calling to join a Guild blessed to be able to rescue those in need - an emergency service guild for those that art stuck and need help - pray consider the Council of Arcana.<br>
<br>
I do again crave thy pardon for changing my mind, yet the Council hast been an institution on Qullious for over three years and it is not a Family that I wish to see dissolve.<br>
<br>
I do apologize again for making another post regarding this issue on thy webpage<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
With Love, Honor and Respect ~<br>
<br>
~ Penny<br>
